  <steps>
    <step num="0">Add the hot water, lemon juice, honey, and star anise to a slow cooker. Stir to combine. </step>
    <step num="1">Turn the heat to high, cover, and warm until the water begins to steam, about 30 minutes. </step>
    <step num="2">Add the black tea bags and let steep for about 8 minutes. Remove the tea bags and reduce the heat setting to warm. </step>
    <step num="3">Add the lemons and whiskey. Stir to combine. </step>
    <step num="4">Ladle into mugs and garnish with lemon wedges. </step>
    <step num="5">Enjoy! </step>
  </steps>
